    <name>Assignment #2: Promoting Mathematical Thinking and Discussion with Effective Questioning Strategies</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Promoting Mathematical Thinking and Discussion with Effective Questioning Strategies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;" color="#000000"&gt;Read the handout, “&lt;a title="PDF - Opens in new window - Promoting Mathematical Thinking and Discussion with Effective Questioning Strategies" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/E368%20M633%20Questioning%20in%20the%20Math%20Classroom_ver2.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Promoting Mathematical Thinking and Discussion with Effective Questioning Strategies&lt;/a&gt;.”  Then, try these strategies with your class and write a one-page reflection.  In your reflection, note what was successful and what was not. You may opt to   record an audiotape of you teaching your class, then review the tape and analyze the questioning behaviors apparent in the recording.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
